{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:psalms.105",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 105,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 105 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:1",
      "text": "O give thanks to the Lord, call on his name, make known his deeds among the peoples!",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:2",
      "text": "Sing to him, sing praises to him, tell of all his wonderful works!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:3",
      "text": "Glory in his holy name; let the hearts of those who seek the Lord rejoice!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:4",
      "text": "Seek the Lord and his strength, seek his presence continually!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:5",
      "text": "Remember the wonderful works that he has done, his miracles, and the judgments he uttered,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:6",
      "text": "O offspring of Abraham his servant, sons of Jacob, his chosen ones!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:7",
      "text": "He is the Lord our God; his judgments are in all the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:8",
      "text": "He is mindful of his covenant for ever, of the word that he commanded, for a thousand generations,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:9",
      "text": "the covenant which he made with Abraham, his sworn promise to Isaac,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:10",
      "text": "which he confirmed to Jacob as a statute, to Israel as an everlasting covenant,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:11",
      "text": "saying, “To you I will give the land of Canaan as your portion for an inheritance.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:12",
      "text": "When they were few in number, of little account, and sojourners in it,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:13",
      "text": "wandering from nation to nation, from one kingdom to another people,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:14",
      "text": "he allowed no one to oppress them; he rebuked kings on their account,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:15",
      "text": "saying, “Touch not my anointed ones, do my prophets no harm!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:16",
      "text": "When he summoned a famine on the land, and broke every staff of bread,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:17",
      "text": "he had sent a man ahead of them, Joseph, who was sold as a slave.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:18",
      "text": "His feet were hurt with fetters, his neck was put in a collar of iron;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:19",
      "text": "until what he had said came to pass the word of the Lord tested him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:20",
      "text": "The king sent and released him, the ruler of the peoples set him free;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:21",
      "text": "he made him lord of his house, and ruler of all his possessions,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:22",
      "text": "to instruct his princes at his pleasure, and to teach his elders wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:23",
      "text": "Then Israel came to Egypt; Jacob sojourned in the land of Ham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:24",
      "text": "And the Lord made his people very fruitful, and made them stronger than their foes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:25",
      "text": "He turned their hearts to hate his people, to deal craftily with his servants.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:26",
      "text": "He sent Moses his servant, and Aaron whom he had chosen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:27",
      "text": "They wrought his signs among them, and miracles in the land of Ham.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:28",
      "text": "He sent darkness, and made the land dark; they rebelled against his words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:29",
      "text": "He turned their waters into blood, and caused their fish to die.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:30",
      "text": "Their land swarmed with frogs, even in the chambers of their kings.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:31",
      "text": "He spoke, and there came swarms of flies, and gnats throughout their country.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:32",
      "text": "He gave them hail for rain, and lightning that flashed through their land.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:33",
      "text": "He smote their vines and fig trees, and shattered the trees of their country.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:34",
      "text": "He spoke, and the locusts came, and young locusts without number;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.35",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:35",
      "text": "which devoured all the vegetation in their land, and ate up the fruit of their ground.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.36",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:36",
      "text": "He smote all the first-born in their land, the first issue of all their strength.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.37",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 37,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:37",
      "text": "Then he led forth Israel with silver and gold, and there was none among his tribes who stumbled.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.38",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 38,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:38",
      "text": "Egypt was glad when they departed, for dread of them had fallen upon it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.39",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 39,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:39",
      "text": "He spread a cloud for a covering, and fire to give light by night.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.40",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 40,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:40",
      "text": "They asked, and he brought quails, and gave them bread from heaven in abundance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.41",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 41,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:41",
      "text": "He opened the rock, and water gushed forth; it flowed through the desert like a river.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.42",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 42,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:42",
      "text": "For he remembered his holy promise, and Abraham his servant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.43",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 43,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:43",
      "text": "So he led forth his people with joy, his chosen ones with singing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.44",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 44,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:44",
      "text": "And he gave them the lands of the nations; and they took possession of the fruit of the peoples' toil,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:psalms.105.45",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 105,
      "verseNumber": 45,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 105:45",
      "text": "to the end that they should keep his statutes, and observe his laws. Praise the Lord!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
